result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander J Enk was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent to each other.  If probation becomes revoked, the defendant is to receive credit for 3 days served.

miscConds.notes: Court orders the $500.00 cash bond on file be applied to the court costs.

records.addlTxt:
2:15 p.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court with Atty Kristina Sander-Brown.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by the Court - PSI sentencing on 2014CF95 & 2015CF71.  Atty Kristina Sanders Brown concurs - defendant will waive the preliminary hearing on 2015CF127.  Defendant concurs.

2015CF127 - Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.

State files an information with the court.  Attorney Sanders-Brown and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Sanders-Brown enters a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of the defendant.  Court sets for Plea & Sentencing Hearing on March 29, 2016 at 3:00 p.m.

Atty Sanders Brown has received a copy of the presentence investigation report, with no corrections, additions or deletions.  State has received a copy of the presentence investigation report, with no corrections, additions or deletions.  Sentencing argument by DA Christenson.  Sentencing argument by Atty Sanders-Brown.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

EACH COUNT/CASE (2014CF95 & 2015F71)

SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 3 years - concurrent to each other.

CONDITIONS (EACH)

-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
-Defendant is not to be in possession of illegal drugs, drug paraphernalia or prescription medication without permission from the agent.
-Continue with treatment / counseling.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
-Defendant is not to associate or affiliate with any known drug users or dealers or be in any establishment where drugs are being sold or used.
-Find and maintain full time employment or search for employment.
-No possession of any firearms.
-2015CF71 - 75 hours of community service.
-Court costs.  Court orders the $500.00 cashon file in 2015CF71 be applied to the court costs first in this case then to 2014CF95.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.
-2014CF95-6 months county jail - no sentence credit and to commence immediately.

Court grants the defendant  sentence credit of 3 days on each case if probation is revoked.

Court adjourned at 2:33 p.m.
to counsel with copy of pre-sentence investigation report
to Agent Bret Grant - request for extension to file PSI has been granted.
from Agent Bret Grant - requests an extension of 30-40 days to file the PSI

9:37 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Kristina Sanders-Brown.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Sanders-Brown - defendant will plea to count 1 on 2014CF95 and count 1 on 2015CF71, with all other counts and cases being dismissed and read-in.  Defendant concurs.  State concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 on 2015CF71 & count 1 on 2014CF95.  Court orders all other counts and cases are to be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Court orders a PSI is to be conducted and filed with the court within 60 days.

Sentencing is scheduled on January 4, 2016 at 9:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:45 a.m.

11:41 a.m.  No appearance by the defendant.  Attorney Kristina Sanders-Brown present.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Sanders-Brown - still needs to talk with the DA in regards to all cases.  Court sets for hearings on October 12, 2015 at 8:30 a.m.  Mandatory appearance or warrant will be issued.

Court adjourned at 11:43 a.m.

1:35 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Kristina Sanders-Brown.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Sanders-Brown confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court notes bond has been set.  Statement by Atty Sanders-Brown - victim is here and requests the no contact be dropped.  Statement by DA Christenson in regards to the no contact provision - objects.  Court questions victim.  Statement by the victim - has not spoke with anyone from the Christine Ann Center.  Court instructs defendant regarding his/her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant will waive the preliminary hearing on 2015CF71, 2015CF72 & 2015CF66.  Defendant concurs.

Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination in 2015CF66, 2015CF71, 2015CF72.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelims and binds the defendant over for trial.  

State files an information with the court for 2015CF66 & 2015CF71.  Attorney Sanders-Brown and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Sanders-Brown enters a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of the defendant.  Court will set for Arraignment in 2015CF72 and Status Hearing on September 1, 2015 at 11:30 a.m.

Court adjourned at 1:43 p.m.

1:03 p.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs defendant of his/her right to an attorney.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 cash bond.  Court instructs defendant regarding his/her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant waives the time limits.  Court will set for Status Hearing on July 28, 2015 at 2:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 1:07 p.m.
